PRUDENTIAL INSURANCE COMPANY OF AMERICA, Complainant, v. LIBERDAR HOLDING CORPORATION, Defendant. SAME, Complainant, v. LAND ESTATES, Inc., Defendant. Staten Island National Bank and Trust Company, Appellant. Nos. 398, 399. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 12, 1936. Jerome L. Greenberg, of New York City, for appellant. Phillip F. Seigenfeld, of New York City, for appellee.

Before L. HAND, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeals dismissed in open court upon the ground that the appellant has no standing in this court.
